com.ibm.team.repository.common

Class ThreePartRepositoryException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • com.ibm.team.repository.common.TeamRepositoryException
          • com.ibm.team.repository.common.ThreePartRepositoryException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class ThreePartRepositoryException
extends TeamRepositoryException
    A repository exception that can contain a 3-part message. This can be used for errors that are appropriate for showing directly to the end user. These exceptions can be easily serialized into a form that can be used by the jazz.ui.MessageBox widget.

    Since this is a repository exception, it can generally be thrown from public API methods without breaking backwards compatibility.

    Since:
    6.0.3
    See Also:

      • cleanMessage

        public static java.lang.String cleanMessage(java.lang.String message)
        Cleans common exception junk out of messages to make them more presentable to users. Use on messages of unknown origin of if they are just known to be ugly.
        Parameters:
        message - any exception message.
        Returns:
        a slightly prettier message. Ideally and lovingly hand crafted message would be used, but many times there is no other information except the opaque message from, say, a TeamRepositoryException.
